com.serena.dmclient.api
Class Filter

java.lang.Object
  com.serena.dmclient.api.Filter

public class Filter
extends java.lang.Object

Concrete class that represents a filter for use when querying a Dimensions server.

This class acts as a container for instances of the inner classes Filter.Criterion and Filter.Order. Adding instances of these classes to this object builds up a filter which can be passed into query and get methods in the API.

There are two constructors for Filter.Criterion, one is blank and one takes three parameters; attributeNumber, value and flags. attributeNumber is the number of the attribute against which the filter is to be applied, or a value from the FilterOptions class. value is the value which records must match to be selected. flags is a bitwise value that may be a logical OR of any of ANY_ROW, EQUALS, GREATER, GREATER_EQUAL, IGNORE_CASE, LESS, LESS_EQUAL, NOT or RELATIONSHIP.

For example, to get a list of all worksets that are children of a workset whose names begin with a 'W':

Filter filter = new Filter();
filter.criteria().add(new Filter.Criterion(SystemAttributes.OBJECT_ID, "W%", Filter.Criterion.EQUALS));
List childWorksets = myWorkset.getChildWorksets(filter);
Or to get a list of all worksets that are INFO-related children of a workset:

Filter filter = new Filter();
filter.criteria().add(new Filter.Criterion(FilterOptions.INFO_RELATIONSHIP, Boolean.TRUE, 0));
List childWorksets = myWorkset.getChildWorksets(filter);
Or to get a list of all worksets that are INFO-related children of a workset whose names begin with a 'W':

Filter filter = new Filter();
filter.criteria().add(new Filter.Criterion(FilterOptions.INFO_RELATIONSHIP, Boolean.TRUE, 0));
filter.criteria().add(new Filter.Criterion(SystemAttributes.OBJECT_ID, "W%", Filter.Criterion.EQUALS));
List childWorksets = myWorkset.getChildWorksets(filter);
 And to have that list returned in reverse order of object ID:

Filter filter = new Filter();
filter.criteria().add(new Filter.Criterion(FilterOptions.INFO_RELATIONSHIP, Boolean.TRUE, 0));
filter.criteria().add(new Filter.Criterion(SystemAttributes.OBJECT_ID, "W%", Filter.Criterion.EQUALS));
filter.criteria().add(new Filter.Order(SystemAttributes.OBJECT_ID, Filter.Order.DESCENDING));
List childWorksets = myWorkset.getChildWorksets(filter);
